<div id="middlecolumn1"><div class="multipageheading"><h1>Welcome to&nbsp;<strong>Community and Living</strong></h1><div class="multipagegraphic"><img width="70" height="70" src="/shared/graphics/kmbc/images/community.gif" alt="Logotype for Community and Living" /></div>
</div>
<h2 class="subhead">Community grants</h2><div style="clear:both;">Knowsley Council works with local 
people, businesses and community 
groups to run programmes (groups of 
related projects) which use European 
Funding to help businesses start and 
grow in Knowsley and to help Knowsley 
people develop the skills to work in 
these businesses.<br />
<br />
The whole of Merseyside is eligible 
for funding (known as Objective One) 
provided by the European Union to 
improve the economy. This money which 
Knowsley is eligible for comes from 
two different funds:<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>The European Regional Development Fund (ERDF)</h2>This aims to improve economic 
prosperity and social inclusion by 
investing in projects to promote a 
successful and diverse local economy.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>The European Social Fund (ESF)</h2>This funds training, human resources 
and 
equal opportunities schemes to promote 
employability of people.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Other Community Grants</h2>Aside from European funding there are a range of other grants available, for which certain organisations may be able to apply for.  A system, to enable relevant grants to be identified is provided on the link below.  <br />
<br />
You will be required to register your organisations details in order to enter the system. <br />
<br />
This information is used for monitoring purposes, to gauge the usage of the system<br />
<br />
<a tabindex="322" title="http://www.open4community.info/knowsley1/Default.a" href="/shared/javascript/common/logging_script.php?transtype=Providing+access+to+community,+professional+or+business+networks&amp;pidno=-1&amp;path=http://www.open4community.info/knowsley1/Default.aspx" target="new">http://www.open4community.info/knowsley1/Default.a (Opens in new window)</a></div>
<br />
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Who can apply</h2>There is no restriction: public, 
private and voluntary sector bodies 
can all make applications. However 
there are strict controls in place to 
ensure that only projects that are 
really going to make a worthwhile 
contribution get funded and also to 
make sure that these projects deliver 
what they promise.<br />
<br />
</div>
